events.name: Auburn Tigers at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: — Mac Jones passed for 302 yards and five touchdowns, highlighted by two long ones to DeVonta Smith, and No. 1 Alabama rolled over rival No. 22 Auburn 42-13 on Saturday without coach Nick Saban.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jones, No. 1 Bama roll past No. 22 Auburn 42-13 minus Saban

events.name: Pittsburgh Panthers at Clemson Tigers

headlines.description: — Trevor Lawrence threw for 403 yards and two touchdowns in his first game in five weeks — and likely last one at Death Valley — as No. 4 Clemson throttled Pittsburgh 52-17 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 4 Clemson, QB Lawrence throttle Pittsburgh 52-17

Kentucky Wildcats at Florida Gators

headlines.description: — Florida’s Kyle-to-Kyle connection returned in a big way after a two-week hiatus and put the sixth-ranked Gators on the verge of the Southeastern Conference championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trask finds Pitts for 3 TDs, No. 6 Florida tops Kentucky

Maryland Terrapins at Indiana Hoosiers

headlines.description: — Stevie Scott III ran for three touchdowns and No. 12 Indiana had three interceptions, three sacks and a game-changing safety in a 27-11 win over Maryland on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 12 Indiana shines on defense in 27-11 win over Maryland

events.name: Coastal Carolina Chanticleers at Texas State Bobcats

headlines.description: — C.J. Marable ran for 157 yards and three touchdowns and No. 16 Coastal Carolina wrapped up the Sun Belt Conference East Division title with a 49-14 victory over Texas State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 16 Coastal Carolina tops Texas State, wins Sun Belt East

events.name: Texas Tech Red Raiders at Oklahoma State Cowboys

headlines.description: — Oklahoma State's top two running backs were out with injuries. Dezmon Jackson played, and that was enough for the Cowboys.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson's 3 TD runs lead No. 21 Oklahoma St past Texas Tech
